        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued November 25 at 3:55PM CST by NWS Birmingham AL</headline>
        <description>At 355 PM CST, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Talladega National Forest, or near Centreville, moving east at 40
mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Centreville, Jemison, Thorsby, Lawley, Talladega National Forest,
Chilton County Motor Sports Park, Gap Of The Mountain, Randolph,
Minooka Park, Trio, I 65 Rest Area, and Bibb County Airport.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

A Tornado Watch remains in effect until 600 PM CST for central
Alabama.</instruction>
